Japanese:
//Text $1BA1C8
#WRITE(ptr,$191D9C)
おにぎりが出るストラップ。[LINE]
愛情を込めて丁寧に握りました。[LINE]
旅のお供に最適。[END]
English:
//Text $1BA1C8
#WRITE(ptr,$191D9C)
Strap with some Rice Balls.[LINE]
Carefully molded with love.[LINE]
One's best traveling companion.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1BA120
#WRITE(ptr,$191DCC)
サンドイッチが出るストラップ。[LINE]
野菜とハムをサンドしたもの。[LINE]
どこでも手軽に食べられます。[END]
English:
//Text $1BA120
#WRITE(ptr,$191DCC)
Strap with a vegetable and ham[LINE]
sandwich. Can be easily eaten[LINE]
anywhere.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1BA068
#WRITE(ptr,$191DFC)
ハンバーガーが出るストラップ。[LINE]
ジューシーなハンバーグをパンで[LINE]
挟みました。ボリューム満点！[END]
English:
//Text $1BA068
#WRITE(ptr,$191DFC)
Strap with a Hamburger. A juicy[LINE]
beef patty between two buns...[LINE]
Very filling![END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B9FC0
#WRITE(ptr,$191E2C)
ホットドッグが出るストラップ。[LINE]
細長いパンに切れ目を入れ、温めた[LINE]
ソーセージをはさんだもの。[END]
English:
//Text $1B9FC0
#WRITE(ptr,$191E2C)
Strap with a Hotdog. Hot sausage[LINE]
in a lengthwise-cut long bun.[LINE]
[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B9F30
#WRITE(ptr,$191E5C)
ブリトーが出るストラップ。[LINE]
ライス・肉・豆・野菜などの具を[LINE]
トルティーヤで巻いたもの。[END]
English:
//Text $1B9F30
#WRITE(ptr,$191E5C)
Strap with a Burrito. Rice, meat,[LINE]
beans, and vegetables wrapped[LINE]
in a tortilla.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B9EA0
#WRITE(ptr,$191E8C)
ケバブが出るストラップ。[LINE]
串に刺した肉をゆっくりと回しなが[LINE]
らじっくり焼き上げたもの。[END]
English:
//Text $1B9EA0
#WRITE(ptr,$191E8C)
Strap with a Kebab. Slowly and[LINE]
carefully roasted skewered[LINE]
meat.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B9E10
#WRITE(ptr,$191EBC)
いなり寿司が出るストラップ。[LINE]
甘く煮た油揚げの中にすし飯を詰め[LINE]
たもの。お子様にも人気。[END]
English:
//Text $1B9E10
#WRITE(ptr,$191EBC)
Strap with an Inarizushi. Sushi with[LINE]
sweet boiled, deep-fried, vinegared[LINE]
tofu. Popular with children.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B9D90
#WRITE(ptr,$191EEC)
一夜漬けが出るストラップ。[LINE]
一夜で漬けた漬物。[LINE]
あっさりして食べやすい。[END]
English:
//Text $1B9D90
#WRITE(ptr,$191EEC)
Strap with a Pickled Vegetables.[LINE]
Vegetables pickled overnight.[LINE]
Easy to eat.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B9CF8
#WRITE(ptr,$191F1C)
お茶漬けが出るストラップ。[LINE]
ご飯に薄味のだし汁をかけて食べる[LINE]
もの。さらさらっとかっ込めます。[END]
English:
//Text $1B9CF8
#WRITE(ptr,$191F1C)
Strap with an Ochazuke. Rice with[LINE]
flavored tea-based broth. Gulped[LINE]
down with a slurping sound.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B9C60
#WRITE(ptr,$191F4C)
チャーハンが出るストラップ。[LINE]
肉や野菜・卵などをまぜて油で炒め[LINE]
味をつけた焼き飯。単品でも満足。[END]
English:
//Text $1B9C60
#WRITE(ptr,$191F4C)
Strap with Fried Rice. Rice fried[LINE]
in oil with meat and vegetables.[LINE]
Simple but filling.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B9BC0
#WRITE(ptr,$191F7C)
オムライスが出るストラップ。[LINE]
ケチャップご飯にトロトロ卵を被せ[LINE]
たもの。子供たちの大好物。[END]
English:
//Text $1B9BC0
#WRITE(ptr,$191F7C)
Strap with Omelette Rice. Ketchuppy[LINE]
Rice folded in an Omelette. A favorite[LINE]
of children.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B9B18
#WRITE(ptr,$191FAC)
カレーライスが出るストラップ。[LINE]
リンゴとハチミツ入り。甘くて少し[LINE]
スパイシー。家庭の味です。[END]
English:
//Text $1B9B18
#WRITE(ptr,$191FAC)
Strap with Curry Rice. Made with[LINE]
apple and honey. Sweet but slightly[LINE]
spicy. Tastes like home.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B9A78
#WRITE(ptr,$191FDC)
オムハヤシが出るストラップ。[LINE]
オムライスとハヤシライスの合体！[LINE]
ボリュームタップリで贅沢な味です。[END]
English:
//Text $1B9A78
#WRITE(ptr,$191FDC)
Strap with Minced Meat Omelette. A fusion[LINE]
between Minced Meat Rice and Omelette[LINE]
Rice. Voluminous and extravagant in taste.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B99E0
#WRITE(ptr,$19200C)
パエリアが出るストラップ。[LINE]
米に肉や魚介類を入れ、オリーブ油[LINE]
とサフランを加えて煮込んだもの。[END]
English:
//Text $1B99E0
#WRITE(ptr,$19200C)
Strap with a Paella. Contains rice,[LINE]
meat, and seafood, stewed with[LINE]
olive oil and saffron.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B9948
#WRITE(ptr,$19203C)
オリエンタルライスが出るストラップ。[LINE]
にらと豚バラ肉をご飯にのせ[LINE]
たもの。スタミナ抜群！[END]
English:
//Text $1B9948
#WRITE(ptr,$19203C)
Strap with Oriental Rice.[LINE]
Rice with chives and pork[LINE]
rib. Packed with stamina.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B98A8
#WRITE(ptr,$19206C)
マフィンが出るストラップ。[LINE]
ふくらませた小さな丸い菓子パン。[LINE]
生クリームをつけるのもお勧め。[END]
English:
//Text $1B98A8
#WRITE(ptr,$19206C)
Strap with a Muffin. Small, round, and [LINE]
puffy sweet pastry. The one stuffed with [LINE]
fresh cream is recommended.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B9820
#WRITE(ptr,$19209C)
キムチが出るストラップ。[LINE]
辛いものが苦手な人は要注意。[LINE]
匂いも味も刺激的。[END]
English:
//Text $1B9820
#WRITE(ptr,$19209C)
Strap with Kimchi. Those who can't [LINE]
handle spicy stuff be cautious. Has[LINE]
a stimulating smell and taste.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B9788
#WRITE(ptr,$1920CC)
肉まんが出るストラップ。[LINE]
一口食べれば口いっぱいに肉汁が！[LINE]
寒い日は食べたくなる一品。[END]
English:
//Text $1B9788
#WRITE(ptr,$1920CC)
Strap with a Meat Bun. Fills the mouth[LINE]
with meat juices when bit into. The sort[LINE]
of stuff one wants to eat on cold days.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B96F0
#WRITE(ptr,$1920FC)
ロコモコが出るストラップ。[LINE]
ご飯の上にハンバーグと目玉焼き。[LINE]
シンプルだけどめちゃうまい！[END]
English:
//Text $1B96F0
#WRITE(ptr,$1920FC)
Strap with Loco Moco. Rice topped[LINE]
with steak and a sunny-side up[LINE]
egg. Simple, but delicious.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B9660
#WRITE(ptr,$19212C)
牛丼が出るストラップ。[LINE]
牛肉をネギなどと煮て、汁とともに[LINE]
どんぶり飯に。忘れられない味。[END]
English:
//Text $1B9660
#WRITE(ptr,$19212C)
Strap with a Beef Bowl. Rice bowl[LINE]
topped with stewed meat and green[LINE]
onions. Unforgettable taste.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B95D0
#WRITE(ptr,$19215C)
親子丼が出るストラップ。[LINE]
甘く煮た鶏肉を卵でとじました。[LINE]
白飯と一緒にお食べください。[END]
English:
//Text $1B95D0
#WRITE(ptr,$19215C)
Strap with an Oyakodon. Rice topped[LINE]
with stewed chicken and egg in a bowl.[LINE]
Please eat it with rice.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B9538
#WRITE(ptr,$19218C)
海鮮丼が出るストラップ。[LINE]
新鮮な魚介類をご飯の上へ。季節に[LINE]
よって素材も変わる。贅沢な一品。[END]
English:
//Text $1B9538
#WRITE(ptr,$19218C)
Strap with a Seafood Bowl. Rice topped[LINE]
with fresh seafood. Its ingredients change[LINE]
with the seasons. A luxurious dish.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B9490
#WRITE(ptr,$1921BC)
クラムチャウダーが出るストラップ。[LINE]
ハマグリとベーコン・野菜などを[LINE]
煮込んだスープ。寒い日にどうぞ。[END]
English:
//Text $1B9490
#WRITE(ptr,$1921BC)
Strap with Clam Chowder. Soup with[LINE]
simmered clams, bacon, and various[LINE]
vegetables. Wonderful on cold days.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B93F8
#WRITE(ptr,$1921EC)
リゾットが出るストラップ。[LINE]
油で炒めた米に肉や魚、キノコで炒[LINE]
めたスープを含ませたもの。[END]
English:
//Text $1B93F8
#WRITE(ptr,$1921EC)
Strap with a Risotto. Rice, meat,[LINE]
fish, and mushrooms stir-fried[LINE]
in oil.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B9348
#WRITE(ptr,$19221C)
ビーフストロガノフが出るストラップ。[LINE]
牛肉をサワークリームのソースで煮[LINE]
込んだもの。贅沢で上品なお味。[END]
English:
//Text $1B9348
#WRITE(ptr,$19221C)
Strap with Beef Stroganoff. Beef[LINE]
stewed in sour cream sauce. Has[LINE]
an extravagant and luxurious flavor.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B92A8
#WRITE(ptr,$19224C)
ミートソースが出るストラップ。[LINE]
タマネギとひき肉はたっぷりと。[LINE]
ソースの跳ねに要注意。[END]
English:
//Text $1B92A8
#WRITE(ptr,$19224C)
Strap with Meat Sauce. Packed[LINE]
with onion and ground meant.[LINE]
Beware of splashing.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B9208
#WRITE(ptr,$19227C)
グラタンが出るストラップ。[LINE]
たっぷり具材にたっぷりチーズ。焦[LINE]
げたチーズの香りは空腹を誘います。[END]
English:
//Text $1B9208
#WRITE(ptr,$19227C)
Strap with Gratin. A plethora of ingredients[LINE]
bathed in cheese. The smell of scorched[LINE]
cheese wets one's appetite.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B9178
#WRITE(ptr,$1922AC)
グラスパが出るストラップ。[LINE]
グラタンとスパゲッティを同時に[LINE]
楽しめる逸品！まずは一口。[END]
English:
//Text $1B9178
#WRITE(ptr,$1922AC)
Strap with Spaghetti Gratin. Allows[LINE]
one to enjoy Spaghetti and Gratin [LINE]
at the same time. Give it a try.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B90E0
#WRITE(ptr,$1922DC)
ハンバーグが出るストラップ。[LINE]
つけ合わせは甘く煮たにんじんを。[LINE]
よく捏ねるほど美味しくなります。[END]
English:
//Text $1B90E0
#WRITE(ptr,$1922DC)
Strap with a Hamburger Steak.[LINE]
Simmered with carrots. Well[LINE]
kneaded to deliciousness.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B9040
#WRITE(ptr,$19230C)
ステーキが出るストラップ。[LINE]
厚く切った肉をただ焼くだけ！[LINE]
肉の素晴らしさが実感できます。[END]
English:
//Text $1B9040
#WRITE(ptr,$19230C)
Strap with a Steak. Just a grilled[LINE]
slab of meat. One can feel the[LINE]
splendor of meat coming off it.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B8F98
#WRITE(ptr,$19233C)
お好み焼きが出るストラップ。[LINE]
水で溶いた小麦粉にお好みの具を。[LINE]
トッピングにかつお節と青ノリを。[END]
English:
//Text $1B8F98
#WRITE(ptr,$19233C)
Strap with an Okonomiyaki. Fried batter[LINE]
garnished to one's preferences. Top it[LINE]
with Nori and and bonito slices.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B8F00
#WRITE(ptr,$19236C)
すき焼きが出るストラップ。[LINE]
牛肉を鉄鍋で甘辛く焼いて煮たもの。[LINE]
お米と一緒に食べても合います。[END]
English:
//Text $1B8F00
#WRITE(ptr,$19236C)
Strap with Sukiyaki.Simmered[LINE]
sweet-salty beef in an iron pot.[LINE]
Also goes well with rice.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B8E70
#WRITE(ptr,$19239C)
お刺身が出るストラップ。[LINE]
新鮮な魚介類を薄く切ったもの。[LINE]
プリプリとした身がたまらない。[END]
English:
//Text $1B8E70
#WRITE(ptr,$19239C)
Strap with Sashimi. Fresh thinly[LINE]
sliced seafood. Irresistibly tender.[LINE]
[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B8DD0
#WRITE(ptr,$1923CC)
舟盛りが出るストラップ。[LINE]
新鮮な魚介類を伝統にのっとって[LINE]
盛りつけました。まだ生きてます。[END]
English:
//Text $1B8DD0
#WRITE(ptr,$1923CC)
Strap with a Sushi Boat.[LINE]
Traditionally arranged fresh[LINE]
seafood. Still alive.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B8D28
#WRITE(ptr,$1923FC)
フルーツパフェが出るストラップ。[LINE]
色々なフルーツを生クリームや[LINE]
アイスにトッピング。甘くてウマイ。[END]
English:
//Text $1B8D28
#WRITE(ptr,$1923FC)
Strap with a Fruit Parfait. Topped[LINE]
with fruits, cream, and ice cream.[LINE]
Deliciously sweet.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B8C80
#WRITE(ptr,$19242C)
フルーツチーズが出るストラップ。[LINE]
すり潰したフルーツと牛乳を混ぜて[LINE]
チーズにする。おやつにピッタリ！[END]
English:
//Text $1B8C80
#WRITE(ptr,$19242C)
Strap with Fruit Cheese. Cheese[LINE]
mixed with milk and mashed fruit.[LINE]
Perfect for a snack![END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B8BD8
#WRITE(ptr,$19245C)
フルーツとうふが出るストラップ。[LINE]
とうふとフルーツを混ぜた、[LINE]
なんともいえない食感の食べ物。[END]
English:
//Text $1B8BD8
#WRITE(ptr,$19245C)
Strap with Fruit Tofu. A mix[LINE]
of tofu with fruits. Has an [LINE]
indescribable texture.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B8B48
#WRITE(ptr,$19248C)
肉鍋が出るストラップ。[LINE]
お肉がメインの鍋。肉の出汁が[LINE]
たまりません。残りはうどんでも。[END]
English:
//Text $1B8B48
#WRITE(ptr,$19248C)
Strap with a Hot Pot. Meat hot pot.[LINE]
Filled with meat stock. Leftover[LINE]
soup can be eaten with Udon.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B8AB8
#WRITE(ptr,$1924BC)
魚鍋が出るストラップ。[LINE]
魚がメインの鍋。魚の出汁がたまり[LINE]
ません。残りは雑炊にどうぞ。[END]
English:
//Text $1B8AB8
#WRITE(ptr,$1924BC)
Strap with a Fish Hot Pot. Filled[LINE]
with fish stock. Leftover soup can[LINE]
be eaten with Rice.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B8A30
#WRITE(ptr,$1924EC)
まんぼうの串焼きが出るストラップ。[LINE]
美味しく食べる事が大事です。[LINE]
[END]
English:
//Text $1B8A30
#WRITE(ptr,$1924EC)
Strap with a Sunfish Skewer. Because[LINE]
eating delicious stuff is important.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B8988
#WRITE(ptr,$19251C)
みそおでんが出るストラップ。[LINE]
甘みのある上質な味噌たれが口の中[LINE]
で染み渡る。お酒の共にも最適です。[END]
English:
//Text $1B8988
#WRITE(ptr,$19251C)
Strap with Miso Oden. The sweetness[LINE]
of fine miso sauce spreads in one's[LINE]
mouth. Goes well with sake.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B88E8
#WRITE(ptr,$19254C)
マーボーカレーが出るストラップ。[LINE]
軍に伝わる秘伝の味。二つの辛味が[LINE]
織り成す究極のハーモニー！[END]
English:
//Text $1B88E8
#WRITE(ptr,$19254C)
Strap with Mabo Curry. A secret handed[LINE]
down by the military. The utmost harmony[LINE]
between pungent and spicy![END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B8858
#WRITE(ptr,$19257C)
カチカチおにぎりが出るストラップ。[LINE]
歯が弱い人は要注意。[LINE]
顎が鍛えられます。[END]
English:
//Text $1B8858
#WRITE(ptr,$19257C)
Strap with a Crunchy Riceball.[LINE]
People with weak teeth beware.[LINE]
Tempers one's jaw.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B87B8
#WRITE(ptr,$1925AC)
パサパサンドイッチが出るストラップ。[LINE]
なるべく早くに食べましょう。[LINE]
喉につまってしょうがない。[END]
English:
//Text $1B87B8
#WRITE(ptr,$1925AC)
Strap with a Dry Sandwich. Eat it[LINE]
as quickly as possible. Getting it[LINE]
stuck in your throat is inevitable.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B8710
#WRITE(ptr,$1925DC)
圧縮ハンバーガーが出るストラップ。[LINE]
誰かのお尻の下敷きになったに違い[LINE]
ない。食べやすくはなりました。[END]
English:
//Text $1B8710
#WRITE(ptr,$1925DC)
Strap with a Squashed Burger. Not[LINE]
much different from a sat-on burger.[LINE]
Easy to eat.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B8680
#WRITE(ptr,$19260C)
炭ドッグが出るストラップ。[LINE]
焼きすぎた！すっかり焦げた[LINE]
ソーセージは苦い味がした。[END]
English:
//Text $1B8680
#WRITE(ptr,$19260C)
Strap with a Burned Dog.[LINE]
Overcooked! A bitter and[LINE]
completely burned sausage.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B85E0
#WRITE(ptr,$19263C)
しなしなブリトーが出るストラップ。[LINE]
だいぶ時間が過ぎちゃった？[LINE]
溶けて固くなったチーズが悲しい。[END]
English:
//Text $1B85E0
#WRITE(ptr,$19263C)
Strap with a Soggy Burrito.[LINE]
Left out for too long. Sadly,[LINE]
the melted cheese solidified.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B8550
#WRITE(ptr,$19266C)
半生ケバブが出るストラップ。[LINE]
お肉はしっかり焼いてください。[LINE]
お腹が痛くなりませんように……[END]
English:
//Text $1B8550
#WRITE(ptr,$19266C)
Strap with a Half-baked Kebab.[LINE]
Please, cook meat properly. So[LINE]
you won't hurt your stomach....[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B84B8
#WRITE(ptr,$19269C)
闇丼が出るストラップ。[LINE]
様々なものがつっこまれた恐怖の丼。[LINE]
まずい日もあれば美味い日もある？[END]
English:
//Text $1B84B8
#WRITE(ptr,$19269C)
Strap with a Dark Bowl. Dreaded Bowl[LINE]
filled with mystery ingredients. Some[LINE]
days it's good, some days it's bad.[END]

Japanese:
//Text $1B8430
#WRITE(ptr,$1926CC)
闇鍋が出るストラップ。[LINE]
何が入っているのかわからない！[LINE]
食べる時は暗闇で。[END]
English:
//Text $1B8430
#WRITE(ptr,$1926CC)
Strap with a Dark Pot. No one[LINE]
knows what's inside it. Better[LINE]
eaten in the dark.[END]
